President Muhammadu Buhari has sent condolences to the former governor of Ekiti State, Mr. Ayo Fayose, over the death of his older sister, Mrs. Moji Ladeji. The President, in a statement issued by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Mr. Femi Adesina, said also mourned with the immediate family of the deceased, praying for the repose of the soul of the departed. “President Muhammadu Buhari prays God’s comfort for former Governor of Ekiti State, Ayo Fayose, on the sad loss of his immediate elder sister, Mrs. Moji Ladeji. “The President equally condoles with the nuclear family of the deceased, the larger Fayose and Ladeji families, friends, relations and associates, urging them to take heart, since death is the ultimate end of all mortals. “President Buhari prays that the soul of the departed will rest in peace,” the statement said.